            <entry xml:id="entry_aræn" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:id="form_d2270e66" type="lemma"><orth>aræn</orth></form>
                <sense xml:id="sense_d2270e69"><sense xml:id="sense_d2270e70"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>межа</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>abutment</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense xml:id="sense_d2270e79"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>граница</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>border</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <re xml:id="re_d2270e89">
                    <form xml:id="form_d2270e91" type="lemma"><orth>fæs-aræn</orth></form>
                    <sense xml:id="sense_d2270e94"><sense xml:id="sense_d2270e95"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>заграница</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>foreign land</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense><sense xml:id="sense_d2270e104"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>за границей</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>abroad</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp xml:id="exampleGrp_d2270e115">
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d2270e117">
                        <quote>aj ta syxagīmæ kajag wyd arænæj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>этот часто затрагивал межу соседа</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>this one often touched the neighbor's border</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>75</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d2270e136">
                        <quote>(næ zæxxæn) ajvazæm jæ aræntæ kardy komæj, toppy fynʒæj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>раздвинем границы нашей земли острием сабли, дулом ружья</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>let's push the boundaries of our land with the edge of a saber, the
                                barrel of a gun</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Хар._Кадӕг"/><biblScope>11</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d2270e155" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>næ zongæj æmæ <note type="comment">(sic!)</note></quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>…не зная границ</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>without knowing the boundaries</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">?</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">?</note><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Gurdž._Æduli"/><biblScope>100</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d2270e184">
                        <quote>næbal es nur aræntæ xumtæn</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>между пашнями нет больше межей</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>there is no more border between arable land</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_AK"/><biblScope>II 50</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d2270e203">
                        <quote>fæsarænæj næm wazǵytæ ærcyd</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>к нам приехали гости из-за границы</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>guests from abroad came to us</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d2270e219">
                        <quote>xūryskæsæjnag arabbyty padcax jæ warænyl ærbalæwwyd æd
                            æfsædtæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>восточный арабский царь явился к его границе с войском</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the eastern Arab king came to his border with the army</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III
                            48</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Хотя по форме <hi rendition="#rend_italic">aræn</hi> представляется отглагольным образованием
                    от <ref type="xr" target="#entry_aryn"/> ‘находить’ („место нахождения“), однако
                    семантически такое толкование мало удовлетворяет. Кроме того, если в пользу
                    связи с глаголом <hi rendition="#rend_italic">aryn</hi> можно было бы указать на то, что в юго-осетинских
                    говорах, где этот глагол звучит <hi rendition="#rend_italic">waryn</hi>, ‘межа’ соответственно зовется
                    <hi rendition="#rend_italic">waræn</hi> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III
                            48</biblScope></bibl>), то, с другой стороны, в дигорском при <ref type="xr" target="#entry_erun"/> ‘находить’, соответствующем и. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_aryn"/>, имеем <hi rendition="#rend_italic">aræn</hi> (а не <hi rendition="#rend_italic">eræn</hi>) ‘межа’,
                    ‘граница’. Приходится поэтому думать о каком-то другом корне *<hi rendition="#rend_italic">ar</hi>-, быть
                    может о том, который отложился в <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d2270e306" xml:id="mentioned_d2270e251" xml:lang="hit"><lang/>
                        <w>arha-</w>
                        <gloss><q>граница</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d2270e315" xml:id="mentioned_d2270e260" xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>arana-</w>
                        <gloss><q>чужой</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d2270e323" xml:id="mentioned_d2270e268" xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>далекий</q></gloss></mentioned> (ср. ос. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærnæg"/> ‘дикий’). Не связано ли ос. <hi rendition="#rend_italic">aræn</hi> с <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d2270e331" xml:id="mentioned_d2270e276" xml:lang="cv"><lang/>
                        <w>jəran</w>
                        <gloss><q>межа</q></gloss></mentioned>? Об осетино-чувашских языковых связях
                    см. под словом <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cyxt"/>
                            ‘сыр’.%n<bibl><author>Bailey</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_TPhS"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1954, стр. 137 сл., 151</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Although <hi rendition="#rend_italic">aræn</hi> seems to be a derivative of the verb <ref type="xr" target="#entry_aryn"/> ‘find’ (“a place where something is
                    found”), according to its form, however, semantically, this interpretation is
                    not very satisfying. In addition, if one could indicate in favour of the
                    connection with the verb <hi rendition="#rend_italic">aryn</hi> that in the South Ossetic dialects where this
                    verb sounds <hi rendition="#rend_italic">waryn</hi>, the ‘boundary’ is accordingly called <hi rendition="#rend_italic">waræn</hi>
                            (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III
                            48</biblScope></bibl>), then on the other hand, in Digor, while having
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_erun"/> ‘find’ corresponding Iron <ref type="xr" target="#entry_aryn"/>, there is <hi rendition="#rend_italic">aræn</hi> (and not <hi rendition="#rend_italic">eræn</hi>)
                    ‘abutment’, ‘border’. Therefore, we have to think about some other root
                    *<hi rendition="#rend_italic">ar</hi>-, perhaps about the one that is found in <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d2270e251" xml:id="mentioned_d2270e306" xml:lang="hit"><lang/>
                        <w>arha-</w>
                        <gloss><q>border</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d2270e260" xml:id="mentioned_d2270e315" xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>arana-</w>
                        <gloss><q>foreign</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d2270e268" xml:id="mentioned_d2270e323" xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>distant</q></gloss></mentioned> (cf. Ossetic <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærnæg"/> ‘wild’). Is the Ossetic <hi rendition="#rend_italic">aræn</hi> connected with
                        <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d2270e276" xml:id="mentioned_d2270e331" xml:lang="cv"><lang/>
                        <w>jəran</w>
                        <gloss><q>abutment</q></gloss></mentioned>? See the information about the
                    Ossetic-Chuvash language connections under the word <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cyxt"/> ‘cheese’.%n<bibl><author>Bailey</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_TPhS"/><biblScope xml:lang="en">1954, p. 137 ff.,
                            151</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
